Sessions
---------
tmux ls ==> list all the tmux sessions
tmux -2 ==> start a new tmux session
tmux attach -t (session_id) ===> attach to the tmux session specified by the id.
Ctrl_B + d ===> detach from the session

Windows
--------
Ctrl_B + c ==> Create a new tmux window
Ctrl_B + n ==> Go to the next window cyclically

Panes
------
Ctrl_B + % ==> Split vert
Ctrl_B + " ==> Split horiz
Ctrl_B + o ==> go between panes
Ctrl_B + x ==> close the plane
Ctrl_B + z ==> toggle hiding the pane

# For multi exec we can do this.
# Add this in ~/.tmux.conf
# Toggle synchronized panes with Prefix + e
bind e run-shell 'tmux setw synchronize-panes $( [ "$(tmux show -v synchronize-panes)" = "on" ] && echo off || echo on )'
